article.headline: Hofstra 71, W. Michigan 68
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Charles Jenkins scored 19 points, including seven in overtime, to lead Hofstra to a 71-68 victory over Western Michigan Saturday in a second-round game of the Charleston Classic. Tony Dennison added 18 for the Pride (1-1). David Kool led Western Michigan (0-2) with 24 points -- 19 in the second half. With Hofstra trailing 59-58, Pride center Dane Johnson made one of two free throws to tie the game with 13.6 seconds to play. Kool missed a baseline jumper for the Broncos and the game went to overtime. Western Michigan led 31-26 at the half after holding Hofstra to 4-of-27 shooting from the field. Hofstra will play East Tennessee State (1-1), and Western Michigan (0-2) faces Southern Illinois-Edwardsville (0-2) on Saturday.
